Change to md5 as default and update HashRing signature

commit.message:
switch to md5 implementation as default, change the hashring signature

This change was motivated by the fact that the ketama hash function has more chances of collisions and thus requires a complete ring regeneration when the nodes topology change. This could lead to degraded performances on rapidly
changing or unstable environments where nodes keep going down and up. The md5 implementation provides a linear performance when adding or removing a node from the ring!

split ring implementations into modules, faster md5 ring rewrite

This work is related to issue #6 reported by @bjhockley

The main idea is to split the ketama implementation from the md5
or user configurable one to overcome some ketama logic problems.

This is required because ketama ring growth and shrink trigger a
full recalculation of the ring which is not efficient for rapidly
changing environments. The performance drawback is pretty bad.

The md5 (or customizable hash function) implementation now offers
a linear performance for growth and shrink operations inspired
from the openstack/tooz project.

IMPORTANT: this first step is meant to be backward compatibile.
